<plan xmlns="http://www.eclipse.org/project/plan" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" name="QVT Operational">
   <release projectid="modeling.m2m.qvtoml" version="3.1.0"/>
   <introduction>
   		<html:p>This document lays out the feature and API set for the fourth annual release of the QVT Operational Project (M2M QVT-OML), version 3.1.0.  This project plan inherits from the Modeling Project Plan, which should be referenced when consulting this individual project plan.</html:p>
   </introduction>
   <release_deliverables>
     <html:p>
    The release deliverables for the M2M QVTO 3.1 have the same form as is found in most Eclipse projects, namely:
<html:ul>
<html:li>QVT Operational source code release.</html:li>
<html:li>QVT Operational SDK (includes runtime and tooling components, with sources, examples, and documentation) (downloadable and update site).</html:li>
<html:li>QVT Operational runtime binary distribution (downloadable and update site).</html:li>
<html:li>QVT Operational tests (downloadable and update site)</html:li>
</html:ul>
</html:p>
      	<html:p>M2M QVTO 3.1.0 source code will be available as versions tagged "R3_1" in the project's CVS repository.
	<html:p>
    </release_deliverables>
   <release_milestones>
      <preamble>
      	<html:p>Release milestone occurring at roughly 6 week intervals and follow the Platform milestone releases by approximately 2 weeks; that is, until the final 3.7 release of the Platform, upon which QVT Operational and other projects will release simultaneously. As QVT Operational is dependent upon the EMF, MDT, and other projects, which are scheduled to release milestones within 1 week of Platform milestones, QVT Operational will deliver its milestones within the following week. It is anticipated that QVT Operational will synchronize its release milestones with the Indigo release schedule.</html:p>
      </preamble>
      <milestone date="Monday 18 August 2010" milestone="3.1.0 M1"></milestone>
      <milestone date="Monday 27 September 2010" milestone="3.1.0 M2"></milestone>
      <milestone date="Monday 8 November 2010" milestone="3.1.0 M3"></milestone>
      <milestone date="Monday 13 December 2010" milestone="3.1.0 M4"></milestone>
