      <milestone date="Monday 16 May 2011" milestone="3.1.0 RC1"></milestone>
      <milestone date="Monday 23 May 2011" milestone="3.1.0 RC2"></milestone>
      <milestone date="Monday 30 May 2011" milestone="3.1.0 RC3"></milestone>
      <milestone date="Monday 6 June 2011" milestone="3.1.0 RC4"></milestone>
      <milestone date="Monday 22 June 2011" milestone="3.1.0 Indigo"></milestone>
      <postamble>
      	<html:p>QVT Operational will produce maintenance releases to align with the Helios SR releases, that includes the Eclipse Platform 3.6.1 and 3.6.2 releases. QVT Operational may produce interim maintenance releases in addition to these in order to satisfy clients requests.
<html:ul>
<html:li>September 24, 2010 - QVT Operational 3.0.1 maintenance release (Helios SR1)</html:li>
<html:li>A list of issues indicated for the 3.0.x maintenance stream can be found in bugzilla.</html:li></html:ul> 
      	</html:p>
      </postamble>
   </release_milestones>
   <target_environments>
   		<html:p>In order to remain current, each Eclipse release targets reasonably current versions of the underlying operating environments.</html:p>
   		<html:p>The QVT Operational component depends upon on the Platform and other projects, which are mostly "pure" Java. The 3.7 release of the Eclipse Platform Project is written and compiled against version 5.0 of the Java Platform APIs, and targeted to run on version 5.0 of the Java Runtime Environment, Standard Edition. QVT Operational will target the same Java version as EMF, which currently requires Java 5.</html:p>
		<html:p>Eclipse Platform SDK 3.7 will be tested and validated on a number of reference platforms. QVT Operational will be tested and validated against a subset of those listed for the platform. Those available will be presented on the project download site.</html:p>
     <internationalization>
     	<html:p>The Eclipse Platform is designed as the basis for internationalized products. The user interface elements provided by the Eclipse SDK components, including dialogs and error messages, are externalized. The English strings are provided as the default resource bundles. As a result, the QVT Operational component will provide English strings in its default bundles and be localized to a subset of those locales offered by the Platform. This plan will be updated to indicate which locales will be provided and the time frame for availability.</html:p>
     </internationalization>
   </target_environments>
   <compatibility_with_previous_releases>
     <html:p>Compatibility of Release 3.1</html:p>
	<html:p>The QVT Operational component will be developed in parallel, and released simultaneously, with the following projects. As stated above, each milestone release of the QVT Operational component will be compatible with the corresponding milestones for each of these projects, and delivered the appropriate offset.</html:p>
	<html:ul>
		<html:li>Eclipse Platform SDK version 3.7</html:li>
		<html:li>Eclipse Modeling Framework (EMF) version 2.7</html:li>
		<html:li>Model Development Tools (MDT OCL) version 3.1</html:li>
	</html:ul>
	<html:p>The QVT Operational 3.1.0 release is backwards compatible with the 3.0.0 releases.</html:p>
   </compatibility_with_previous_releases>
